Ross-- Or maybe I'm just not giving you enough credit. I mean, it is difficult to say goodbye to five people.

239
00:17:45,313 --> 00:17:48,180
Goodbye, goodbye, goodbye, goodbye, g--

240
00:17:48,350 --> 00:17:50,215
It's physically impossible!

241
00:17:53,355 --> 00:17:55,855
You know what? After all we've been through,

242
00:17:55,924 --> 00:17:59,589
l can't believe this is how you want to leave things between us.

243
00:17:59,661 --> 00:18:01,659
Have a good time in Paris.

244
00:18:06,981 --> 00:18:08,780
I hope Ross isn't too upset.

245
00:18:08,852 --> 00:18:12,177
I'm sure he's not more bummed out than I am. Tell me about it.

246
00:18:12,254 --> 00:18:15,155
Well, you can't say we don't know how to throw a party.

247
00:18:16,424 --> 00:18:18,415
I think I'm gonna head out.

248
00:18:19,027 --> 00:18:22,658
Where do you think you're going? I thought I was going home to go to bed...

249
00:18:22,731 --> 00:18:25,991
...but I'm sensing there's something less fun for me to do here.

250
00:18:27,102 --> 00:18:30,200
We're moving in a couple of days, and we got a lot of packing to do.

251
00:18:30,272 --> 00:18:34,368
It'd be great if you guys could pitch in. Joey and I can finish up the guest room.

252
00:18:34,443 --> 00:18:36,240
Ohh yeah yeah, good idea.

253
00:18:37,312 --> 00:18:40,512
Oh, no. You and Phoebe are gonna help me in here.

254
00:18:40,849 --> 00:18:42,676
You couldn't be cool.

255
00:18:45,019 --> 00:18:46,611
OK. We're gonna start in the kitchen.

256
00:18:46,688 --> 00:18:49,916
Plates get put into plate protectors and stacked 10 to a box.

257
00:18:49,991 --> 00:18:53,893
The silverware gets bundled in rubber bands and then bubble wrapped. Got it?

258
00:18:54,062 --> 00:18:56,830
Yeah. Good. I need you to be careful and efficient.

259
00:18:56,897 --> 00:19:01,059
And remember, if I'm harsh with you, it is only because you're doing it wrong.

260
00:19:03,872 --> 00:19:06,864
Hey, Mon, I think I figured out whose handcuffs they are.

261
00:19:06,942 --> 00:19:13,738
You did? How? Well, I was cleaning out the closet and I found some pictures of them being used.

262
00:19:13,747 --> 00:19:17,683
Oh, my God, let me see.

263
00:19:18,086 --> 00:19:19,519
Who's that dirty old lady?

264
00:19:21,189 --> 00:19:22,622
Monica's grandmother.

265
00:19:24,025 --> 00:19:27,620
Nana liked it rough!

266
00:19:29,430 --> 00:19:32,395
Hi. Hey. Come here, have a seat. Yeah.

267
00:19:32,474 --> 00:19:34,842
How was your night? Oh, it was okay.

268
00:19:34,910 --> 00:19:37,440
I went to a movie with my cousin then out for dinner.

269
00:19:37,513 --> 00:19:39,879
We went to this place that had--

270
00:19:44,820 --> 00:19:49,615
Anyway, they had these really amazing cheeseburgers.

271
00:19:51,194 --> 00:19:55,361
Erica, are you okay? Yeah, you know, maybe I ate too much.

272
00:19:55,430 --> 00:20:00,094
I keep getting these stomachaches. They come and go every few minutes.

273
00:20:01,137 --> 00:20:05,540
Oh, my God. Relax, we'll just get her some antacids.

274
00:20:06,408 --> 00:20:09,233
She doesn't have a stomachache! She's in labor!

275
00:20:09,311 --> 00:20:11,579
Oh, my God! Yeah, you gotta get to the hospital!

276
00:20:11,647 --> 00:20:15,906
OK. Chandler, get the coats! Erica, let's go! Phoebe and Joey, keep packing!

277
00:20:15,985 --> 00:20:18,510
Oh, my God, we're gonna have a baby.

278
00:20:18,788 --> 00:20:20,653
We're gonna have a baby!

279
00:20:21,023 --> 00:20:23,116
Oh, my God, we're gonna have a baby!

280
00:20:23,292 --> 00:20:26,489
Oh, God, I've gotta sit down! I've gotta sit down!

281
00:20:28,030 --> 00:20:31,957
Honey, it's gonna be okay. You can do this. Just breathe.

282
00:20:31,968 --> 00:20:34,766
Okay. Okay.

283
00:20:34,937 --> 00:20:37,670
Okay, I feel a little better.

284
00:20:37,740 --> 00:20:39,469
Are you sure?

285
00:20:40,776 --> 00:20:44,136
Yes, I'm sure. Oh, honey, let's go. Okay.

286
00:20:44,146 --> 00:20:46,171
Come on, let's go. Okay, bye, everyone!

287
00:20:46,248 --> 00:20:47,372
We're having a baby! Good luck!

288
00:20:47,450 --> 00:20:49,513
Chandler, wait, wait, wait! What?

289
00:20:49,585 --> 00:20:53,112
If you get a second, find out where she got that cheeseburger.

290
00:21:00,939 --> 00:21:03,931
You think I didn't say goodbye to you because I don't care?

291
00:21:04,109 --> 00:21:05,733
That's what it seemed like.

292
00:21:05,810 --> 00:21:10,509
I cannot believe that after 10 years you do not know one thing about me!

293
00:21:10,682 --> 00:21:15,984
Fine! Then why didn't you say something? Because it is too damn hard, Ross!

294
00:21:16,154 --> 00:21:20,784
I can't even begin to explain to you how much I am gonna miss you.

295
00:21:21,393 --> 00:21:25,625
When I think about not seeing you every day, it makes me not want to go.

296
00:21:26,665 --> 00:21:33,659
Okay? So if you think that I didn't say goodbye to you because you don't mean as much to me as everybody else, you're wrong.

297
00:21:33,705 --> 00:21:36,469
It's because you mean more to me.

298
00:21:36,641 --> 00:21:39,475
So there, all right? There's your goodbye!

299
00:21:39,511 --> 00:21:40,944
Rach! What?

300
00:21:41,112 --> 00:21:43,342
You keep-- You can't-- What?

301
00:22:05,202 --> 00:22:07,432
A little more. Okay.

302
00:22:07,872 --> 00:22:10,640
A little more. A little more. All right.

303
00:22:12,509 --> 00:22:14,739
Little more.

304
00:22:15,613 --> 00:22:19,775
All right. All right, let's do this. All right, ready?

305
00:22:19,850 --> 00:22:22,580
Yep. Now give me your best shot.

306
00:22:22,620 --> 00:22:24,918
All right. Here goes.

307
00:22:29,927 --> 00:22:32,157
Doesn't work.

